Gold Extends Rally to Record, Topping $1,500 an ounce

-- B y   K y o u n g w h a   K i m
-- 
2011-04-20T04:35:47Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-20/gold-extends-rally-to-record-1-500-as-investors-look-for-inflation-hedge.html
Gold extended its rally to record,
topping $1,500 an ounce, as investors sought the metal to guard
against rising inflation and currency debasement.  Gold for immediate delivery climbed as much as 0.3 percent
to $1,500.43 an ounce in  Singapore  today, while bullion futures
for June delivery gained 0.4 percent to $1,500.90.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Kyoungwha Kim at 
 kkim19@bloomberg.net  